I'd be hard-pressed to find one person at the company (other than someone in upper management) that will say they are happy with their job. I've never seen so many unhappy employees throughout any place I've ever worked. It's inevitable that any time employees get together to hang out "away" from work, the "I hate SMT" conversations begin.Do not expect to get paid anywhere close to what the average salary is for your position. You will get the absolute lowest pay possible. Raises are rare and extremely small.There is also not a good balance between work and personal life. Management expects you to make yourself available after hours and on weekends. This leads to tons of stressed and burned-out employees. The work emails never stop.Employees are taken for granted and hard work goes unappreciated and unnoticed for the most part. Even if it is noticed and acknowledged, nothing will come of it. If you're interested in finding a long-term career, stay far, far away from this place. It's quite a shame. You look at this company from the outside and expect that it would be quite a fun and satisfying place to work. Sadly, that's just not the case.Advice to ManagementTake the time to show appreciation for your employees. That can go a long way. Give employees an incentive to go above and beyond. Set up a well-defined career path for each position and pay what they are truly worth.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (9) Sportsmedia Technology Corp Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Sportsmedia Technology Corp 2014-05-02 08:27 PDT Jan 27, 2013"Mixed"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeCurrent Employee - Anonymous EmployeeDoesn't RecommendNeutral OutlookI have been working at Sportsmedia Technology Corp full-timeProsAwesome people, positive work environment, very good work/lif