INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGY COULD HELP AMERICAN FLAG FOOTBALL LEAGUE SOAR




What's New


American Flag Football League
When the AFFL searched for a technology provider, the league tapped SMT, the company that invented the virtual first-down line, handles data integration for Next Gen Stats and provides scoring and statistics for the Super Bowl. 




Featured Product



Ribbon board production
SMT's custom ribbon board productions have been used at events worldwide, including the CrossFit Games, the Waste Management Phoenix Open, the WTA World Finals and the American Flag Football League. Whether displaying timing and scoring, stats, animations, promotions, or sponsor content, SMT's ribbon board productions enhance the Game Day experience.


















Careers - SMT




























Careers



SMT, the leader in scoring systems, graphics software and data integration for live televised sporting and entertainment events, is always interested in hiring talented people motivated to work toward providing cutting-edge technology for broadcast networks, sports teams and venues. We are proud of our achievements: innovative technology, our high-quality team and outstanding service, all of which have helped us win numerous awards, including Emmys, Tellys, Daveys and PromaxBDA Sports Marketing Awards. 
Qualified candidates should sign on to SMT's Career Center.
Benefits
We offer a comprehensive benefits package including:

Health
Dental
Vision
Disability
Life insurance
401k retirement plan 
Flexible Spending Accounts
Paid time off
Relocation assistance

Verifications of employment can be obtained by sending a fax to (919) 283-4301.

                Thank you for taking an interest in SMT.
            



Account Manager


The Account Manager maintains and expands existing client relationships by actively engaging and advising clients on all SMT products and services. The Account Manager will liaison between all of SMT departments (Operations, Engineering, Creative, Help Desk, Accounting, Sales and Marketing) to ensure client expectations are met.




Production Software Engineer


The Production Software Engineer builds upon and tests an SMT base product to customize its graphical style, layout and behavior according to client specifications.




Remote Operations Technician


The Remote Operations Technician provides complete on-site event technical support by collaborating with both office staff and on-site clients to deliver exceptional SMT products while providing excellent customer service. 




Quality Assurance Developer


The QA Developer designs, develops and analyzes SMT test automation methods, frameworks and tools for the purpose of continual improvement and methodical evolution. 













 
































